org.deeplearning4j.parallelism

Class MagicQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.deeplearning4j.parallelism.MagicQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<DataSet>, java.util.Collection<DataSet>, java.util.Queue<DataSet>

    public class MagicQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Queue<DataSet>
    Limited Queue implementation, suited for multi-gpu prefetch. Basic idea is simple: DataSets are coming from DataSetIterator, and their device location is unknown. So, for better performance DataSets should be transparently moved to the devices where they will be used later, and this should be done in background.

      • poll

        public DataSet poll(long time,
                    java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
             throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        This method is supposed to be called from managed thread, attached to specific device. It returns 1 DataSet element from head of the queue, and deletes that element from Queue. If queue is empty, Please note: if there's nothing available in Queue - NULL will be returned
        Parameters:

        timeUnit - TimeUnit for time param
